      "CVE": "CVE-2026-41898",
      "Description": "rust-openssl provides OpenSSL bindings for the Rust programming language.  From 0.9.24 to before 0.10.78, the FFI trampolines behind SslContextBuilder::set_psk_client_callback, set_psk_server_callback, set_cookie_generate_cb, and set_stateless_cookie_generate_cb forwarded the user closure's returned usize directly to OpenSSL without checking it against the \u0026mut [u8] that was handed to the closure. This can lead to buffer overflows and other unintended consequences. This vulnerability is fixed in 0.10.78.",
      "Threats": [
        {
          "Type": "Impact",
          "Severity": "moderate"
        }
      ],
